<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military, Nuclear &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Approves Amendments to Law on Servicemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Approves Amendments to Law on Servicemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306201794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1831 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306201794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 23 TASS -- The Russian Government has 
approved amendments to the existing legislature at its session 
today. A law on the status of servicemen was adopted 
practically without debates and a resolution was adopted to 
submit the law to the president for signing. 
  If the Russian president signs the law, amendments will be 
made to Russian laws on pensions, freedom of religion, income 
tax, tax on property and land, law on employment and the land 
code of the Russian Federation. 
  These amendments will give a number of privileges in social 
welfare to servicemen and their families, envisaged by the 
Russian law on the status of servicemen, taking into account the 
specifics of a military service. 
  In an interview to journalists after the government session 
was over, Russian Defence Minister Pavel Grachev said that all 
privileges earlier granted to servicemen will remain in force. 

</TEXT>

