<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military, Nuclear &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cosmonauts Continue Research on Mir Space Station </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cosmonauts Continue Research on Mir Space Station </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406101594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1004 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Flight Control Centre (Moscow region) June 24 TASS 
-- The Russian cosmonauts continue their mission aboard the Mir 
space station. 
  They conducted geophysical, astrophysical, technological and 
medical experiments this week. The crew was also preparing the 
ballistic capsule of the Progress M-23 ferry for its return to 
the earth. 
  Friday's programme of work includes astrophysical 
experiments 
to study gamma-radiation flows of galactic origin and 
investigation of properties of various materials in open space. 
  Under the medical control programme, investigations will be 
conducted to check up water-salt metabolism and to take clinical 
blood analysis of cosmonauts who experienced zero-gravity 
conditions for a long time. 
  Work in space proceeds according to a preset programme. The 
cosmonauts are healthy and feel well. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

