<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe, 23 June (ITAR-TASS) -- Two attempts at 
armed infiltration into Tajikistan from Afghanistan by small 
groups of Tajik gunmen on sections of the Pyanj border 
detachment, were foiled during the night of 22-23 June by 
Russian border guards. 
  The Directorate of the Group of Russian Border Guards in 
Tajikistan told the ITAR-TASS correspondent that artillery 
strikes were carried out near [border] crossings. It is not 
known if the infiltrators suffered losses. There were no losses 
among the Russian servicemen. 

