<H3> <TI>   More on Visit by Kyrgyzstan's Dzhumagulov </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More on Visit by Kyrgyzstan's Dzhumagulov </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306132294 Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network in 
Kyrgyz 2300 GMT 22 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2306132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kyrgyz </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Summary] Apas Dzhumagulov, the prime minister of 
Kyrgyzstan, paid a visit to Kazakhstan. He was received by the 
president and the prime minister of the Republic of Kazakhstan. 
They discussed the issue of Kazakhstan's payment of debt to 
Kyrgyzstan for power supplies. It was decided that Kazakhstan 
will provide Kyrgyzstan with 1 million tonnes of coal, 100,000 
tonnes of black oil, 3,000 tonnes of gas, and 5,000 tonnes of 
diesel oil as part of a payment for debt. Apart from Apas 
Dzhumagulov, the delegation of Kyrgyzstan included Sultanov, the 
chairman of the republican national bank; the president of the 
joint stock Kyrgyzenergetika power engineering company; the 
general director of the Karabalty ore mining combine; and other 
officials. 

</TEXT>

