<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Supports Introduction of Single CIS Currency </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Supports Introduction of Single CIS Currency </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306114194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 0942 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister of Kazakhstan Sergey Tereshchenko 
believes that Kazakhstan cannot return to the ruble zone due to 
serious economic differences between Russia and Kazakhstan. 
  He told parliament on Thursday [23 June] that it would be 
beneficial to introduce a supra-national CIS currency -- the 
altyn. 
  He said that the idea of introducing the altyn had been 
proposed by President Nazarbayev and that Kazakhstan's 
withdrawal from the ruble zone and the introduction of its 
national currency was a forced measure, taken after Russia 
demanded about $1.5 billion from Kazakhstan. 
  He said that a single economic system must be created, and 
customs limitations lifted in the CIS, all of which will promote 
the integration of the CIS countries. 

</TEXT>

