<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Duma Approves 1994 Federal Budget </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Duma Approves 1994 Federal Budget </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406072194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0704 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406072194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 24 TASS -- The State Duma, the lower 
house of the Russian federal legislature, has finally approved 
the Russian federal budget for 1994 as a whole after months of 
debates. On Friday morning 273 deputies voted for it, with 80 
voting against and eight abstaining. Four deputies, who left 
their electronic voting cards behind, supported the vote in 
favour at the microphones in the hall. 
  The law provides for the spending of 194.5 trillion roubles 
and the revenue of 124.5 trillion roubles. It imposes a cap of 
70 trillion roubles on the budget deficit. 
  Following the approval by the Duma, the law will be 
forwarded 
to the Federation Council. 
  The budget-94 was eventually approved in the fourth round of 
voting after the earlier three rounds on Wednesday failed to 
give the seal of approval to the budget, which the deputies 
found lacking due allocations for defence, health care and 
education. 
  The Duma had to set an hour apart for voting on Friday and 
threatened sanctions to absentees. All scheduled trips were 
cancelled and those on business elsewhere were recalled to 
ensure the quorum. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

