<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Signs European Union Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Signs European Union Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406085994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0815 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406085994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondents Yuriy Sizov, Vladimir </F>
Malyshev, and Yuriy Malinin] 
  [Text] Kerkira (Corfu), 24 Jun -- A full-scale document 
comprising over 80 pages and translated into the 12 [as 
received] languages of the EU [European Union] member-countries 
has not yet been circulated in the press center in Kerkira. 
However, ITAR-TASS correspondents have learned from circles 
close to the Russian delegation that the main aim of the 
agreement is to facilitate trade, investments, and harmonious 
economic relations and to strengthen political and economic 
freedoms. 
  It follows from the agreement that a permanent political 
dialogue is being established between Russia and the EU, which 
both countries intend to develop and make more active. The 
document also envisages meetings between the Russian president 
and the chairmen of the EU Council and Commission. A political 
dialogue at parliamentary level is envisaged to be held twice a 
year. 
  The agreement plans to set up a cooperation council, which 
will monitor the implementation of this historic document. It 
will comprise members of the Russian Federation Government and 
leaders of the EU working bodies. A Parliamentary cooperation 
committee is also being set up. 
  The 10 sections of the agreement pay special attention to 
economic cooperation, including, in particular, articles on 
trade in nuclear materials and financial and cultural 
cooperation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-41439 </DOCNO>
