<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Signing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Signing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406081494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0735 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406081494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondents Yuriy Sizov, Vladimir </F>
Malyshev, Yuriy Malinov] 
  [Text] Kerkira (Corfu), 24 Jun -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin signed a historic document here today -- the agreement 
on partnership and cooperation between the Russian Federation 
and the European Union. Jacques Delors, chairman of the 
European Commission, Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou of 
Greece, which is ending its chairmanship of the European Union, 
as well as the leaders of the other EU member-countries put 
their signatures to the agreement. 
  Speaking at the ceremony, which was held in the church of 
St. 
George, Yeltsin stressed that it was a question of "a document 
of tremendous historical importance," of a decisive step in 
restoring the unity of the European continent. 
  This morning a meeting took place between the Russian 
president and Jacques Delors, the chairman of the European 
commission. 

</TEXT>

