<H3> <TI>   Primakov on N. African Tour, Meets With `Arafat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Primakov on N. African Tour, Meets With `Arafat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306135494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1247 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306135494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By CRIME-TASS correspondent Olga Semenova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 23 TASS -- The director of Russia's 
External Intelligence Service (EIS), Yevgeniy Primakov, is 
already several days into an unofficial tour of North Africa, 
ITAR-TASS learned in the EIS press bureau. The EIS 
representative reported that Primakov had met with Yasir `Arafat 
in Tunis, and had also had a series of conversations with other 
political figures in various countries. 
  While the EIS director's tour is unofficial, his 
peace-keeping mission seems to be fully official. One of the 
most important questions discussed by Primakov during his 
meetings was the Middle East peace process. Primakov was 
assigned the job of talking to leaders in the troubled area not 
so much due to his position as EIS chief, but because he is one 
of Russia's top Middle East experts. 
  At the end of this week, Primakov is expected to return to 
Moscow. 

</TEXT>

