<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peace Talks in Tehran Focus on Cease-Fire Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peace Talks in Tehran Focus on Cease-Fire Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2306153294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1256 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2306153294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The participants in the inter-Tajik talks which 
began in Tehran on June 18 are concentrating on the discussion 
of a cease-fire agreement and on measures to prevent other 
hostile actions. The draft was proposed by the UN special envoy 
Ramiro Piriz Ballon, the Russian Foreign Ministry's spokesman 
Grigoriy Karasin told journalists on Thursday. 
  Karasin believes that the discussion and adoption of the 
agreement is the main goal of the Tehran talks and said that 
Russia hopes both Tajik delegations will reach an understanding 
on the issue. 
  He also said that Russia would continue to assist the 
attainment of mutually acceptable agreements. "Our attitude to 
the parties concerned will depend on how sincerely they approach 
the talks," he said. 

</TEXT>

