<H4>    Yeltsin Departs for Home </H4>

<F P=102> LD2506164594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1604 
GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2506164594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Athens, 25 Jun -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin 
left Athens today for Russia. On 24 June, on the Greek island 
of Corfu, he signed an agreement on partnership and cooperation 
between the Russian Federation and the European Union [EU]. 
Yeltsin was seen off at Athens Airport by Greek National 
Defense Minister Yerasimos Arsenis, Russian Federation 
Ambassador to Athens Valeriy Nikolayenko, and other officials. 
The farewell ceremony was simplified as top Greek leaders are 
staying in Corfu, where the EU summit ended earlier today. 
  The Russian president travelled from Corfu to the port of 
Piraievs in the yacht Alexandros, which had served as his 
residence during the visit. 

</TEXT>

