<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russians `Move' Ahead on Yemen Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russians `Move' Ahead on Yemen Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2406144494 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 24 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM2406144494 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Yusuf Shakir: "Russian Ambassador to Cairo: We </F>
Have Stopped Arms Shipments to Yemen; Our Recognition of South 
Depends on Brahimi's Report"] 
  [Text] Cairo -- Russian Ambassador to Cairo Vladimir 
Polyakov has denied that Russia has provided any military aid to 
the parties to the Yemeni conflict. 
  He revealed that Moscow has stopped sending arms shipments 
to 
the two warring parties. He stressed that his country's 
recognition or nonrecognition of the South Yemen state will be 
determined in the light of the report UN envoy Lakhdar Brahimi 
is to submit to UN Secretary General Dr. Butrus-Ghali. 
  The Russian ambassador said following his meeting yesterday 
with Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid that 
he had informed the League that Moscow has instructed him to 
coordinate positions with the Arab League vis-a-vis the Yemeni 
crisis and to closely monitor what is happening in Yemen. He 
pointed out that Russia supports an immediate cease-fire and the 
initiation of a direct dialogue among the conflicting parties. 
He added that this is in line with the Arab League's position. 
He revealed that the stage ahead will witness a Russian move on 
the current situation in Yemen through the results Brahimi is 
going to reveal in his report on the crisis. However, he did 
not specify the nature of the move. 

</TEXT>

