<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Vladimir Solntsev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 27 TASS -- Chinese Foreign Minister Qian 
Qichen arrives in Moscow on Monday to prepare the second 
Russian- Chinese summit to be held in September when Chinese 
leader Jiang Zemin comes to the Russian capital. 
  The Chinese minister will hold talks in Moscow with his 
Russian counterpart Andrey Kozyrev. Following them, the sides 
will initial several bilateral documents to be signed by the 
Russian and Chinese leaders at the summit. 
  Qian will meet speaker of the Russian parliament upper 
chamber Vladimir Shumeyko and will be possibly received by 
President Boris Yeltsin and cabinet head Viktor Chernomyrdin. 
  Apart from bilateral relations, the sides will discuss, in 
the context of preparations for the summit, the most urgent 
international issues, including the nuclear problem on the 
Korean peninsula. 
  The chinese minister will make a trip to some former Soviet 
republics, which will last till July 2. Qian will depart from 
Moscow for Byelorussia [Belarus] on Wednesday. Then, he will 
visit Lithuania and Estonia. 

