<H3> <TI>   North Atlantic Assembly Delegation Visits St Petersburg </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    North Atlantic Assembly Delegation Visits St Petersburg </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406144194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1332 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Svetlana Ivanova] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg, 24 Jun -- A delegation of 
parliamentarians of the North Atlantic Assembly has arrived in 
the city on the Neva. Today they visited the Taurida Palace -- 
the headquarters of the Inter-Parliamentary Assembly [IPA] of 
the CIS countries. 
  The representatives of the inter-parliamentary organization 
of the 16 NATO member-states were interested in the economic 
situation in the Commonwealth countries and, first and foremost 
in the parliamentary capital of the CIS. During a conversation 
with Mikhail Krotov, the general secretary of the IPA, issues 
related to the conversion of defense enterprises both in St. 
Petersburg and in the CIS as a whole, and problems of attracting 
foreign investments to the former Soviet republics were touched 
upon. In this connection, Krotov stressed the IPA's special 
role in creating the legal basis for the market economy on the 
territory of all the Commonwealth countries and in developing 
international business contacts. 
  The sides expressed mutual interest in strengthening further 
ties between two of the world's major parliamentary structures. 

</TEXT>

