<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Notes Russian Importance to G7 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Federation Council Notes Russian Importance to G7 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406133494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0734 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 24 Jun -- "The developing format of a 
political G8, which includes Russia, must ensure that more 
constructive solutions are reached to pressing international 
problems, solutions based on mutual respect for the interests of 
leading states and their responsibility for international 
security and stability," says a statement which was distributed 
today by the Committee on International Affairs of the Russian 
Federation Council. The statement was issued in connection with 
the summit of G7 countries which will be held in Naples on 9-10 
July. The summit will be attended by Russian Federation 
president Boris Yeltsin. 
  The results of the economic section of the forthcoming 
summit 
meeting will depend in many respects on whether there is a 
readiness to set about real implementation of agreements reached 
at previous summits on support for reform in Russia, a readiness 
to take practical steps to intensify and develop them. The 
statement stresses that "without Russia's participation it is 
difficult to see how many global economic problems, including 
the problem of foreign debt, can be effectively resolved. It 
has to be recognized that Russia is not just a debtor but also a 
creditor. Russia, which has inherited the huge debts owed to 
the former USSR by developing countries, is entitled to 
participate in the evolution of approaches to this problem by 
other creditors of third world countries." 

</TEXT>

