  [Text] Russian border guards in Tajikistan have been put on 
military alert and the units on guard where Russian border 
guards and their families live have been reinforced, Vladimir 
Novikov, chief of staff of the directorate of the Russian border 
guards in Tajikistan, said today in Dushanbe. He also said that 
some of the Russian border guards at the Tajik-Afghan border 
will be transferred to Dushanbe to protect Russian servicemen 
and ethnic Russians living in the city. 

