<H3> <TI>   Reshuffling of Envoys to United States, UK, UN Planned </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reshuffling of Envoys to United States, UK, UN Planned </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406132094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1258 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Nechayev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 24 TASS--Russian Deputy Foreign Minister 
Sergey Lavrov will evidently replace Yuliy Vorontsov as Russian 
U.N. chief delegate if the latter is approved as ambassador to 
the United States. 
  A high-ranking official at the Russian Foreign Ministry who 
refused to be identified, told ITAR-TASS on Friday that "the 
Vorontsov-Lavrov link continues to operate". Lavrov is now in 
New York. Talks that Lavrov may replace Vorontsov at his post, 
started last year for the first time. 
  Lavrov's possible appointment will complete a series of 
planned reshuffling among Russian leading ambassadors. Russian 
First Deputy Foreign Minister Anatoliy Adamishin will evidently 
replace Boris Pankin in London while Vorontsov will most likely 
go to Washington to occupy the post held by Vladimir Lukin, the 
present chairman of lower house Committee on International 
Affairs. 

</TEXT>

