<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 24 Jun -- The State Duma has decided to meet 
in plenary session three times a week during the time remaining 
to the parliamentary recess. Until now it has been holding two 
plenary sessions a week -- on Wednesdays and Fridays. 
  Communist Deputy Igor Bratishchev, who put forward the 
proposal for an additional sitting, noted the Duma had a lot of 
work to complete before deputies went off on their holidays. He 
observed that many deputies were neglecting their duties by not 
attending the Duma regularly. As an example, he cited his 
political opponents in the Russia's Choice group. He claimed 
that "30 percent of Yegor Gaydar's supporters do not turn up for 
plenary sessions." 

