<F P=100> Regional Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Duma Delegation Tours Russian Far East </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Duma Delegation Tours Russian Far East </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606082594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0802 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2606082594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Sergey Borovkov, Pavel </F>
Kuznetsov] 
  [Text] Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky, June 26 (TASS) -- A State 
Duma delegation, led by its speaker Ivan Rybkin, which is 
continuing its working trip to Siberia and the Far East, arrived 
in Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky late on Saturday. 
  In Kamchatka the legislators will meet representatives of 
the 
local government bodies, naval officers and sailors, fishermen 
and workers of fish-processing enterprises. Rybkin will visit 
the famous Geyser valley and Paramushir, one of the Kurile 
islands. 
  Previously the delegation visited Irkutsk, where they took 
part in the work of the Siberian agreement council. It includes 
19 republics, autonomous and national districts, territories and 
regions of Siberia. During the work of the Siberian agreement 
council Rybkin and heads of the main State Duma committees told 
in detail representatives of the executive and legislative 
authorities of Siberian regions about the law-making work of 
the lower chamber of the federal assembly and its prospects. 
  Rybkin told journalists at the airport that the legislators 
"wished to see for themselves the life in those cities, which 
are so far away but are still our, Russian cities, to talk with 
people, to hear the opinion of heads of local administrations. 
We want advice on the best way to divide the pie which is 
called the budget." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

