<H3> <TI>   Delegation Meets Pacific Fleet Command </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegation Meets Pacific Fleet Command </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606122094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1153 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2606122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Sergey Borovkov, Pavel </F>
Kuznetsov] 
  [Text] Petropavlovsk-Kamchatskiy June 26 TASS -- Head of 
the State Duma Ivan Rybkin, who is leading a delegation of the 
lower chamber of the Federal Assembly now touring Siberia and 
the Far East, had a meeting here today with representatives of 
the command of the Russian Pacific Fleet. 
  They discussed at the meeting problems of financing and 
supply of the fleet, Aleksandr Piskunov, deputy chairman of the 
State Duma committee on defence, told ITAR-TASS. The 
conversation also touched upon the problem of the utilisation of 
the used nuclear fuel from reactors of nuclear-powered 
submarines and ammunition. 
  Rybkin told naval officers about the efforts taken by the 
State Duma for finding additional sources of financing for the 
Armed Forces. They discussed tasks facing the Russian Navy in 
connection with the bringing of the strength of the Armed Forces 
in conformity with the mobilising and financial resources of the 
country. 

</TEXT>

