<F P=100> Regional Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Maritime Territory Economy Hit by Miners' Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Maritime Territory Economy Hit by Miners' Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706044594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0248 
GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706044594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yuriy Grachev] </F>
  [Text] Luchegorsk (Maritime Territory), 27 Jun -- The 
northern regions of the Maritime Territory have turned out to be 
on the verge of economic catastrophe. A strike by transport 
workers of the Luchegorsk opencast coal mine, which is the main 
supplier of fuel for the Primorskaya state regional electric 
power station, the giant of far eastern power engineering, has 
been going on for ten days now. The shortfall in deliveries of 
coal over the ten days exceeds 500,000 tonnes. 
  The main reason for the protest action was that the 
transport 
workers' wages are regularly overdue and they have not been paid 
since April. Besides this, the strikers are demanding the 
abolition of tariff cuts, as well as the resignation of the 
director of the main enterprise of "Primorskugol". 
  In their turn, the administration of the transport 
directorate, believing the action to be illegal, have instituted 
court proceedings against the strikers. In response, according 
to a report from Mikhail Byankin, chairman of the strike 
committee, their families will picket the court sitting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

