<H3> <TI>   Pechora Coal Industry Enterprises To Be Restructured </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pechora Coal Industry Enterprises To Be Restructured </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506110694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0919 GMT 25 Jun 1994 </F>
<F P=103> LD2506110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 25 TASS -- The Russian Government has 
instructed the Ministry of Fuel and Power, together with the 
government of the Republic of Komi, to work out by the beginning 
of 1995 a comprehensive programme to restructure coal-industry 
enterprises in the Pechora coal fields, according to a 
government resolution made available to ITAR-TASS on Saturday. 
  The programme is expected to suggest solutions to such 
matters as reconstruction, a rise in the efficiency of promising 
coal mines, the construction of new ones, the employment of 
mineworkers thus released, a gradual relocation of the disabled 
residents of Vorkuta and Inta to other regions of Russia, etc. 
  At the same time the ministry is to substantiate the 
expediency of the continued operation of four coal mines -- 
Yun-Yaga, Promyshelennaya, Yur-Shor, and Yuzhnaya by October 
this year. 
  The government resolution provides for a number of other 
measures as well. 

</TEXT>

