<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lukashenko on First Round Success in Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lukashenko on First Round Success in Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406141794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1359 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406141794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by BELINFORM correspondent Nikolay Nazarovich for </F>
TASS] 
  [Text] Minsk 24 June TASS -- "What has happened came as a 
sensation only for those who refused to face the truth," said 
Belarusian presidential candidate and presidential race leader 
Aleksandr Lukashenko commenting on his success in the first 
round of the elections. 
  "The poor and deprived people for the first time had a 
chance 
to elect their like to the supreme state post, and the people 
said its word," Lukashenko told BELINFORM over the telephone 
today. 
  Speaking of his further plans against corruption, Lukashenko 
said "all the high-ranking officials accused by the 
parliamentary commission against corruption remain on their 
posts. They are ready to do everything to finish the 
construction of their villas." 
  As for his election program, the presidential candidate 
noted 
they have "outlined three areas: To keep in check the inflation 
and price increase, work against corruption and establish close 
economic relations with Russia." 
  Lukashenko's team has elaborated "a block of proposals to 
solve the economic problems, stop the production recession 
within six months, resume the work of enterprises, bring people 
back to their jobs and create more jobs." He said they hope to 
do it with the assistance of Russia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

