<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In an interview with ZVYAZDA on 25 June, Uladzimir 
Zamyatalin, secretary to Belarusian Prime Minister Vyachaslaw 
Kebich, commented on the results of the first round of 
presidential elections. In particular, he said: "The prime 
minister realizes that there have been no elections since 1990. 
He understands the primary motives which guided people during 
the presidential elections. The point is that the people voted 
not against Kebich but against the current developments in the 
Republic." Uladzimir Zamyatalin voiced doubts over fears that 
when Lukashenka comes to power he will begin with repressions. 
  The press secretary refuted rumors that the Kebich team will 
attempt to disrupt the second round of elections. He stated 
that Kebich and his team have not yet discussed his withdrawal 
from the elections. 

