<H3> <TI>   Cited on Cooperation Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cited on Cooperation Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606075294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1638 
GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2606075294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetskiy] </F>
  [Excerpts] Kishinev [Chisinau], 25 Jun -- In the course of 
his official visit to Moldavia [Moldova], Sergey Stepashin, 
director of the Russian Federal Counterintelligence Service 
(FCS), today visited the Dniester region. He went there 
together with Vasile Calmoi, national security minister. During 
the trip the head of the FCS had a meeting in Tiraspol with 
Aleksandr Lebed, commander of the 14th Russia Army, which is 
stationed there, and was acquainted with the operation of its 
special section. 
  The ITAR-TASS correspondent has learned from Tiraspol that 
the meeting with Gen. Lebed was held in camera. Oleg Gudyma, 
deputy security minister of the as yet unrecognized Dniester 
Republic, who arrived at the Army headquarters, was not allowed 
to attend the meeting. Speaking to journalists in Tiraspol, 
Sergey Stepashin said he was satisfied with the agreement on 
cooperation between the Russian FCS and the Moldavian National 
Security Ministry, which was signed in Kishinev 24. [passage 
omitted] 
  On the problem of the Dniester region, representatives of 
the 
Russian FCS said: "It should be settled only peacefully, and 
Russian special services will assist this process using all 
legitimate means." 

</TEXT>

