<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Meets Former French Premier Crisson </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Meets Former French Premier Crisson </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406160094 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1400 GMT 
24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kazakh Foreign Minister Kanat Saudabayev today met 
Former French Prime Minister Edith Crisson. They discussed 
cooperation between Kazakhstan and the European Union. The 
strengthening of integrational processes in the world as whole 
was noted. The minister spoke about the main provisions of the 
Euroasian union formation concept and the future implementation 
of the idea. Edith Crisson displayed interest in President 
Nazarbayev's initiative on creation of the Eurasian union of 
states. She said that she was impressed by the conceptual 
nucleus of this initiative. The ambassador of France to 
Kazakhstan participated in the meeting. 

</TEXT>

