<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fourth Privatization Auction Held in Almaty </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fourth Privatization Auction Held in Almaty </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406161194 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Russian 1400 GMT 
24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406161194 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The fourth privatization auction was held today. 
But one cannot see any special activity going on at privatized 
enterprises. In fact, the giants of industry are never on sale, 
although at this auction the caliber of enterprises varied. 
Among the 45 enterprises offered for sale are those of the 
light industry, fuel and gas supplying, and machine-building. 
  As has been expected, the least demand of the approximately 
100 funds participating in the auction, was in construction 
industry enterprises, because their capacity is small, the 
infrastructure is not there, and the production base is weak. 
But such enterprises as the Akmolinsk spinning and weaving mill 
or the Karagandaodezhda joint stock company were objects of 
serious battles. The outcome of the fourth auction is as 
follows: 85.3 percent of stock were sold. Of 104 funds that 
contested the tenders, 83 funds bought shares. The others lost 
owing to deliberately low starting prices. 

</TEXT>

