<F P=100> RUSSIAN NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Stepashin Calls For Curbing Rights of Criminals </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Stepashin Calls For Curbing Rights of Criminals </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506134494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1256 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2506134494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetskiy] </F>
  [Text] Kishinev June 25 TASS -- "In keeping with the 
current legislation all investigative and operational activities 
will affect people's rights in one way or another. Without this 
it will be impossible to fight crime," Russian 
Counterintelligence Service Chief Sergey Stepashin said. 
  In an exclusive interview with ITAR-TASS on Saturday, 
Stepashin said that "any operational activities inevitably limit 
the rights of criminals. This is an axiom. In this connection 
I would like to say again that I am for violation of the `right' 
of criminals to kill, rob, rape and encroach upon the rights of 
other people and their life. I am for such limitations, 
provided all procedural norms ensuring the calm life of the 
citizens of Russia are observed." 

</TEXT>

