<F P=100> RUSSIAN NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Airs Views on Anticrime Measures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy Airs Views on Anticrime Measures </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406154894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1511 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Nechayev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 24 TASS -- Liberal-Democratic Party 
leader Vladimir Zhirinovskiy believes that the police is so 
corrupted it is unable to carry out anti-crime measures. The 
police should be replaced with retired KGB officers, said 
Zhirinovskiy. 
  In his opinion, the federal counter-intelligence service is 
also unable to suppress crime since it "assists foreign secret 
services". The latter, in their turn, concentrated on the 
Russian Liberal-Democratic Party. Zhirinovskiy thinks that the 
border should be partially closed and citizens of former Soviet 
republics should be prohibited to visit large Russian cities for 
six months in order to make anti-crime measures efficient. 
  "We demand to start anti-crime measures with cleansing of 
the 
Interior Ministry itself, removal of corrupted officials and 
their replacement with retired officers of the KGB, the armed 
forces and the Military Procurator's Office. If the 
high-ranking officials are not replaced, the presidential decree 
(against crime) will become an instrument against political 
opponents and not criminals," Zhirinovskiy told a news 
conference here today. 
  He also demanded to stop "predatory privatization", do not 
hold joint exercises with NATO, do not send Russian peace-makers 
outside the Russian Federation and raise the minimum salary to 
50,000 rubles per month. 

</TEXT>

