<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Predicts Presidential Rule </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy Predicts Presidential Rule </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606153794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1516 
GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2606153794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Evald Kessariyskiy] </F>
  [Text] Nizhniy Novgorod, 26 Jun -- Analyzing the political 
situation in the country, Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of the 
LDPR (Liberal Democratic Party of Russia), has not ruled out the 
possibility of dissolution of the State Duma and introduction of 
direct presidential rule in the next few months. He arrived in 
Nizhniy Novgorod today together with members of the LDPR group 
of deputies in the State Duma. 
  The city's residents showed particular interest in a rally 
held in its main square. At the rally, the party leader 
reiterated that "there has been no real change in the lives of 
the people of Russia following the elections." This is why, 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy explained, "we are in opposition, and if 
we do not succeed in replacing this government, we do not rule 
out the possibility that we ourselves would cancel the Treaty on 
Social Accord we signed earlier." 

</TEXT>

