<H3> <TI>   Lysenko To Head Republican Party of Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lysenko To Head Republican Party of Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606162294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1530 GMT 
26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2606162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The congress of the Republican Party of Russia today 
elected 38-year old Vladimir Lysenko its chairman. He was a 
cochairman of the party jointly with Vyacheslav Shostakovskiy. 
Yesterday, the congress introduced changes to the rules, 
introducing the posts of chairman and deputy chairman instead of 
the institution of cochairmen. Both Lysenko and Shostakovskiy 
are State Duma deputies. They are members of the Yabloko 
faction. Grigoriy Yavlinskiy, leader of the faction, reported 
several days ago that within the next few days the faction would 
discuss the question of expelling Lysenko from the faction, 
because his actions run counter to the stand of the majority. 
  At the congress yesterday, Lysenko spoke out against the 
party going into opposition on a course pursued by the president 
and the government. Shostakovskiy favored a democratic 
alternative to this course. 

</TEXT>

