<H3> <TI>   Council Charts Strategy To Attract Foreign Capital </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council Charts Strategy To Attract Foreign Capital </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706085994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0811 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706085994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Oleg Velichko] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 27 TASS -- The consultative Foreign 
Investment Council attached to the Russian Government is 
entrusted with working out the strategy for investing foreign 
capital to Russia, Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin said in a 
conversation with Western businessmen who have arrived in Moscow 
to participate in the council meeting which opens today. 
  Judging by all appearances, the consultative council will 
mark another phase in rapprochement between the Russian and 
world economies hot on the heels of the Russian president's 
recent successful trip to Corfu and of the prime minister's 
visit to the United States. 
  The council meeting today is to be addressed by Prime 
Minister Chernomyrdin, First Vice-Premier Oleg Soskovets, 
Central Bank Governor Viktor Gershchenko and Acting Finance 
Minister Sergey Dubinin. The leaders of Russian key ministries 
and the departments are taking part in the council meeting. 
  Representatives of transnational corporations of North 
America, Europe and Asia are taking part in the meeting. 
Western businessmen said in the conversation with the Russian 
prime minister that they would like to see a better organisation 
of the consultative council's work. They called for setting up 
panels and deciding on the specific directions of work. 

</TEXT>

