<F P=101> Nuclear &amp; Military Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armed Forces To Be Reduced to 1.5 Million Men </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armed Forces To Be Reduced to 1.5 Million Men </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506163194 Moscow Radio Moscow World Service in English 
1500 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2506163194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow World Service </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev has said that 
his country's military doctrine is directed at no country. 
However, the country has its own national interest and an 
efficient army must defend them, General Grachev said. 
  He was speaking at Tula, a city southward of Moscow. 
Addressing cadets of the Military Artillery School, General 
Grachev said that Russia's Armed Forces would be reduced from 3 
million to 1.5 million men, but the forces would be more mobile 
and strong. 

</TEXT>

