<H3> <TI>   Status of Gas Pipeline Construction to Iran Unsure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Status of Gas Pipeline Construction to Iran Unsure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2506140294 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN in 
English 0646 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2506140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan ("GOLOS ARMENII" Daily-Past), 06/25/94 -- 
It's hard to say for sure, what is the current situation 
regarding the construction of an Iran-Armenia gas pipe-line, 
though official discussions in this regard were being carried 
for several years. The information from official sources is 
quite contradictory. 
  According to RA [Republic of Armenia] Governmental press 
service, the matter is getting no further than negotiations, and 
representatives of both sides continue discussion of 
construction details. 
  At the same time, RA Ministry of Fuel and Energy reported 
that the negotiations have been finished, and projecting work is 
currently being done. 

</TEXT>

