<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Amends Criminal Code </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Federation Council Amends Criminal Code </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406195094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1612 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406195094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Federation Council approved Friday changes and 
amendments of the Russian Criminal and Criminal Proceedings 
Codes. 
  Nearly 40 articles of the former and nine of the latter were 
amended. At the same time 19 Criminal Code articles were 
annulled and 15 new ones included. 
  The Council's Constitutional Legislation and Legality 
Committee issued a statement saying that among important new 
articles were 17 on crimes committed by a conspiring group of 
people or by an organized group and 213 (3) on terrorism that 
were aimed at combatting organized crime. Article 13 on 
necessary defense was revised. The notions of socialist and 
personal properties were removed. 
  The committee said that some changes and amendments of the 
Criminal Code were fundamental in that they had a bearing on the 
main institutions of criminal law and would enhance the 
suppression of crime. 
  Also Friday the Federation Council passed without debate a 
bill adopted by the State Duma on foreign borrowings and credits 
granted by the Russian Federations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

