<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shumeyko Supports Amended Draft Budget </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shumeyko Supports Amended Draft Budget </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406194694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1707 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Speaker of the Federation Council Vladimir Shumeyko 
says he voted in favor of the government-proposed budget for 
1994. Speaking in Moscow, he said his decision came after the 
Council had pushed through new articles to the budget relating 
to government spending on the armed forces. 
  Article 32 now provides for an extra budgetary fund of 
support to the army to be raised as part of government revenues 
from privatization. The resources are to be channelled to 
provide social security nets to the servicemen including housing 
construction and conversion of defense-related industries. 
  One other article binds the government to bring down the 
cost 
of this year's defense spending by offering contracts to men and 
non-commissioned officers and hiring officers in reserve, 
reducing the number of military schools and disbanding 
understaffed contingents. 
  The budget now provides for 40.6 trillion rubles of defense 
spending in 1994. 
  However, the Council did not adopt any resolution on 
Shumeyko's report about FC's role and place in overcoming 
critical trends in the country. The question will be discussed 
as the Council meets again next month. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

