<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia's Choice Opposes Extending Assembly Term </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia's Choice Opposes Extending Assembly Term </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406195294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1811 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The State Duma group of Yegor Gaydar's Russia's 
Choice rejected proposals that the term of the Federal Assembly 
be extended. It insisted on holding parliamentary and 
presidential elections as specified by the constitution. 
  In its statement made public in the Duma Friday the group 
said that its members could not agree with the proposal made by 
Federation Council Chairman Vladimir Shumeyko. 
  The statement said that Russia's Choice was giving priority 
to legality and morality over political expediency. It cast 
doubt on the desirability of what Shumeyko had proposed. The 
Russia's Choice group considers that instead of consolidating 
political stability it would destroy the weak saplings of civic 
accord, trust between political groupings and respect for the 
law that had emerged in Russian society recently. 
  The group is not convinced by Shumeyko's argument that the 
extension of the terms would save much funds. It states that 
society had paid dearly for every short cut of democratic 
procedures. What is more, it would be members of parliament who 
would make a decision on extending their own terms, which would 
place them in a delicate moral position. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

