<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian, CSCE Officials Cable Aliyev on Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian, CSCE Officials Cable Aliyev on Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2406202794 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2406202794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vladimir Kazimirov, the plenipotentiary 
representative of the Russian President, and Jan Eliasson, 
chairman of CSCE Minsk Group, sent a letter to Azerbaijani 
President Geydar Aliyev. 
  The cable says: Esteemed Mr. President, during the 
consultations held in Moscow on 22 and 23 June concerning the 
resolution of the Karabakh conflict, we noted with satisfaction 
that the cease-fire called for on 12 May through the Russian 
mediation and CSCE's support is generally being observed. The 
cease-fire agreement that has been ratified with the signatures 
of the defense ministers and army commanders is an essential 
factor for ending the dispute. However, we express our 
uneasiness at the human loss and material damage recently caused 
by several clashes on the Armenian-Azerbaijan border. We regard 
any attempt to violate the cease-fire as dangerous. 
  Within the framework of our joint efforts, we call on all 
the 
sides to adhere to the following in order to end the conflict: 
  1. The sides should demonstrate in words and deeds their 
loyalty to the obligations they have undertaken in signing the 
cease-fire agreement. 
  2. The sides should avoid any hostile activity that may 
undermine the atmosphere of confidence, which is being created. 
  3. The sides should take adequate [preceding word in 
English] measures to peacefully resolve and remove the existing 
disputes. 
  4. With a view of signing a political agreement to end the 
armed conflict and in order to further activate the peace 
process, the sides should resolutely take advantage of the 
existing peaceful situation. They should make a strenuous 
effort to put into effect the clear demand for an end to the 
bloody conflict between the people and the solution of all the 
contentious issues at the negotiating table. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

