<H3> <TI>   Advisor Comments on Message </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Advisor Comments on Message </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2406204194 Baku Radio Baku Network in Azeri 1700 GMT 24 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2406204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Radio Baku Network </F>
<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 20 June, Jan Eliasson, chairman of the CSCE Minsk 
Group, and Vladimir Kazimirov, President Boris Yeltsin's special 
envoy, conveyed a joint letter to President Geydar Aliyev, 
President Levon Ter-Petrosyan, and the head of the Armenian 
community in Daghlyk Karabakh on the need for the consolidation 
of the cease-fire agreement in the region. An AZERTAC 
correspondent has asked Vefa Gulizade, state adviser on foreign 
policy affairs, to comment on the letter. He said the following: 
  I wish to stress that the letter is the initial outcome of 
the effective cooperation between the CSCE and the Russian 
Federation. Jan Eliasson held talks with [name and title 
indistinct], First Deputy Foreign Minister Adamishin [name as 
heard], and Vladimir Kazimirov in Moscow during the past few 
days. The need to find a peaceful solution to the dispute 
between Armenia and Azerbaijan within the CSCE framework was 
emphasized. The representatives of the nine CSCE Minsk Group 
members will meet in Vienna on 7 July. Vladimir Kazimirov will 
also attend that meeting. The most important point in the 
letter is the call to the disputing sides to take advantage of 
the cease-fire and sign a political agreement to completely end 
the bloody confrontation and move to resolve all the problems 
through talks. 

</TEXT>

