<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev Meeting With Kazimirov Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aliyev Meeting With Kazimirov Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2606190394 Baku Radio Baku Network in Azeri 1700 GMT 26 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2606190394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Radio Baku Network </F>
<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Geydar Aliyev received Vladimir Kazimirov, 
President Yeltsin's competent envoy on the Daghlyk Karabakh 
problem, today. Aliyev and Kazimirov agreed that the cease-fire 
is not being heeded in the western areas and that the existing 
situation requires that the principles must be consolidated so 
that a peaceful solution can be found to end the war. 
  Vladimir Kazimirov briefed Geydar Aliyev on CSCE Minsk Group 
Chairman Jan Eliasson's visit to Moscow and his talks with 
Vladimir [name indistinct], chairman of the Russian Federation 
[word indistinct] and chairman of the CIS Interparliamentary 
Assembly, and Deputy Foreign Minister Adamyshin. He said that 
the main issue that was discussed was the question of finding a 
peaceful solution to resolve the dispute between Armenia and 
Azerbaijan. He noted that the outcome of the talks indicated 
that Russia and the CSCE maintained a similar approach. In view 
of that, the sides must benefit from the political experience 
and positions of Russia and the CSCE. 
  President Aliyev said that he highly assesses the talks Jan 
Eliasson has held with the political circles in Russia. He 
described the general agreement reached between the 
representatives of the CSCE and Russia as a concrete step in the 
effort to find a peaceful solution to the war. 
  Later, the sides discussed the possibility of benefiting 
from 
the experience of the Middle East countries and Turkey, which 
are neighbors with Armenia and Azerbaijan. Geydar Aliyev noted 
that the participation of the representatives of Iran and Turkey 
in the effort to find a political solution to the problem is 
essential. He also said that holding political consultations 
with them is equally important. 
  State Adviser Vefa Gulizade and Foreign Minister Gasan 
Gasanov attended the meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

