<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kazimirov, Aliyev Support Turkish Role </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kazimirov, Aliyev Support Turkish Role </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2606183294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2606183294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Omer Kebapcioglu report from Baku] </F>
  [Text] Vladimir Kazimirov, President Yeltsin's special 
envoy to Nagorno-Karabakh, who is conducting shuttle diplomacy 
to solve the Azerbaijani-Armenian conflict, arrived in Baku 
again last night. He was received by President Geydar Aliyev 
this morning. Kazimirov said Russia believes the active 
participation of Turkey and Iran in the efforts to resolve the 
Nagorno-Karabakh problem would be beneficial. He explained that 
he went to Tehran to hold talks with this aim and that Iran 
agreed to the proposal in principle. Kazimirov said he will soon 
go to Ankara with the same proposal. 
  Aliyev said he finds the proposal favorable. He said he 
supports the current developments, which started with a 
cease-fire and continued with a letter sent to the leaders of 
the sides concerned. The active participation of Turkey and 
Iran, Aliyev said, might make a solution easier. 
  Aliyev pointed out that Turkey is a member both of the CSCE 
and of the Minsk Group. In this respect, he said, we attach 
great importance to the participation of Turkey in particular. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

