<H3> <TI>   Nakhichevan Statement Notes Armenian Truce Violation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nakhichevan Statement Notes Armenian Truce Violation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2406154294 Baku TURAN in English 1102 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2406154294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku (June 23) TURAN: Today the press service of 
Nakhichevan's Supreme Mejlis issued a statement which reads that 
having violated the truce agreement, Armenian troops launched an 
attack towards the villages of Yukhary and Ashagy Buzgov in the 
Babek region on June 18 and on June 19-20 towards the Sadarak 
Region of Nakhichevan. 
  Earlier on May 28 Armenian troops attacked the village of 
Gunnet in the Sadarak Region and moved 1 kilometre further into 
Nakhichevani territory. Armenians seized several strategically 
important hills and shelled the region centre of Sadarak. As a 
result five Azeri soldiers have been wounded and several 
housings have been damaged. 
  However, after that attack the representatives of Armenia 
and 
Nakhichevan reached the agreement banning escalation of tension 
on the border. Resumption of aggressive activities shows that 
Armenia's authorities ignore the efforts by the international 
organizations aimed at restoration peace in the region. 
  The press service of Supreme Mejlis of Nakhichevan calls on 
the world community to exert pressure in the Republic of Armenia 
to stop its aggression against Nakhichevan Autonomous Republic. 

</TEXT>

