<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev Remarks on Worsening State of Economy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aliyev Remarks on Worsening State of Economy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2406143794 Baku TURAN in English 1101 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2406143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku (JUNE 23) TURAN: Today newspaper "AZERBAIJAN" 
published a report of a session devoted to current economic 
problems, held on June 21 by President Aliyev. 
  He noted that despite the taken measures the situation in 
economic sphere worsens. It was noted at the session that low 
prices for energy sources at inner market and preferential 
allocation of credits ruined social and economic sphere. In 
these connection positive assessment was given to President's 
decrees on quarterly revise of prices for oil and oil products 
and preferential allocation of credits. 
  Head of the Parliament Rasul Guliyev noted that despite 
President's decree "Liberalization of Foreign Trade" there is a 
great quantity of unsold goods in the warehouses. So in the 
warehouses of the Ministry for Agriculture are kept unsold goods 
total 400 million dollars, in SOCAR [Azerbaijan State Oil 
Company] -- 100 million dollars, State Committee for Metallurgy 
-- 15-20 million dollars. The amount of unsold goods totals 600 
million dollars. Products totalling 5-6 million dollars spoil 
every day. 
  The issue of privatisation of incomplete construction 
objects 
was also discussed at the session. 
  Rasul Guliyev noted again that "economic reforms should be 
conducted in all spheres and simultaneously". 

</TEXT>

