<H3> <TI>   Presidential Committee Examines Economic Problems </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Presidential Committee Examines Economic Problems </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2706053194 Yerevan SNARK in English 1749 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2706053194 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Business SNARK" file] </F>
  [Text] Baku [no dateline as received] -- An advisory 
committee headed by Geydar Aliyev had a session June 21 where 
present problems in Azerbaijan economy were discussed. 
  The President certified that, though the necessary measures 
were undertaken, the situation in economy is aggravated. Low 
prices for fuel at domestic market, as well as easy-terms 
credits played a destructive role in the social and economic 
sphere. 
  In this connection, positively were estimated the 
President's 
orders on quarterly revisions of prices for oil and petroleum 
products and on granting credits on easy terms. 
  Parliament Chairman Rasul Guliyev, appearing on the session, 
observed that despite the President's order "On Liberalization 
of Foreign Trade Prices", an enormous amount of goods in the 
state warehouses remain non-distributed. Thus the Agricultural 
Ministry has goods for $400m [million], State Oil Concern for 
$100m, and State Metal Concern from $15m to $20m. Total price 
of unsold goods is $600m. Every day products for a sum $5m to 
$6m turn unfit. 
  Mr. Guliyev proposed to organize a special advisory 
commission with powers to distribute the stored products in 6 
months period. 
  The session also discussed the issue of privatization of 
unfinished construction sites. 

</TEXT>

