<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tbilisi Reports Activities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tbilisi Reports Activities </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606142594 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1300 
GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2606142594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The CONTACT news agency has supplied us with 
information from the head of state's press secretariat. A group 
of journalists from the head of state's press secretariat is 
working in the conflict zone of Abkhazia. According to their 
information, the distribution of the CIS peace-keeping forces 
deployed at the Roki hippodrome to initial positions started 
during the morning of 26 June. Three convoys have already left 
for Jvari, Anaklia, and Rukhi. Engineers who are preparing 
border checkpoints together with signallers who are to establish 
a connection have joined the positions of the southern zone. 
  Blue helmets have appeared for the first time today bearing 
the caption: "Peacekeeping forces." There are approximately 21 
units of heavy weaponry that have been distributed to Analkia, 
Jvari, and Rukhi. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

