<H3> <TI>   Poll Finds People Optimistic About Troop Presence </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Finds People Optimistic About Troop Presence </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2506111094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 25 Jun 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> MK2506111094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "NEGA Reports" rubric] </F>
  [Text] A poll held by Georgia's sociological services 
indicates that 44.9 percent think that the bringing of 
peacekeeping troops to Abkhazia will help restore Georgia's 
territorial integrity; 38.7 percent think the bringing of 
peacekeeping forces will have no influence on the restoration of 
Georgia's territorial integrity, and 16 percent found the 
question hard to answer. 

</TEXT>

