<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abkhazia Conditions Bridge Repairs on Truce Guarantees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abkhazia Conditions Bridge Repairs on Truce Guarantees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406135294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1344 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406135294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Irina Shchegoleva] </F>
  [Text] Sochi June 23 TASS -- Abkhazia conditioned on Friday 
the beginning of repair works at two major bridges over the 
border river of Inguri on firm guarantees that they would not be 
used by Georgia for combat purposes. 
  Deputy Premier Enver Kapba, the chief Abkhazian negotiator 
at 
the current talks with Georgia, told ITAR-TASS that all repair 
works at the motor bridge will start only after Russian 
peacekeepers are deployed to separate the conflicting parties. 
  "As far as the railway bridge is concerned, (Abkhazia) will 
start repair works only when the problem of its political status 
is settled," Kapba stressed. 
  The deputy premier told TASS that Abkhazia had handed over 
to 
the Georgian side a list of valuables removed from the Abkhazian 
territory during the war. The list included aircraft, sea 
vessels, motor vehicles, factory equipment and museum rarities 
among other things. 
  "To continue our dialogue, it is essential that the Georgian 
side reimburse at least a part of that damage," Kapba said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

