<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze, Armenians Discuss Relations, Abkhazia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shevardnadze, Armenians Discuss Relations, Abkhazia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506165294 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1210 
GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2506165294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An Armenian parliamentary delegation headed by 
Deputy Speaker Aram Saakyan arrived in Tbilisi today. The 
delegation had a meeting with Eduard Shevardnadze, the chairman 
of the Georgian Supreme Council and head of state. The 
conversation dealt with fruitfully developing relations between 
Armenia and Georgia. 
  Problems common for the two countries have been considered. 
In particular, the Armenian representatives pointed out that 
the return of refugees to Abkhazia is very important for them, 
too, because a lot of ethnic Armenians, who have also been 
affected by the conflict, live in Abkhazia. Shevardnadze has 
said that the Georgian side will appreciate the involvement of 
the Republic of Armenia in the settlement of the issue. 
  The conversation also touched upon the work of the two 
parliaments. The sides have shared their experience. 
  The meeting was attended by Vakhtang Rcheulishvili, the 
deputy speaker of the Georgian Supreme Council. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

