<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Defense Ministry Collegium Discusses Problems </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Defense Ministry Collegium Discusses Problems </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406193094 Tbilisi First Program Television Network in 
Georgian 1600 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi First Program Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A meeting of the Georgian Defense Ministry's newly 
appointed collegium was held on 23 June. The meeting was 
conducted by Lieutenant Genereal Vardiko Nadibaidze, the 
Georgian defense minister. Personnel problems, the provision of 
foodstuffs and material, and technical resources were the 
subjects of the straight talk held at the meeting. The defense 
minister sharply criticized some senior officials of the 
ministry for a lack of responsibility and negligence in their 
work that has caused a just resentment among the personnel in 
some of the military units. It has been indicated that a 
detailed program for the improvement of the current situation is 
to be worked up. Members of the military collegium of the 
Defense Ministry, as well as Armed Forces commanders have to be 
actively involved in the implementation of this program. Urgent 
assistance has been requested from the government and the 
authorities of the republic. 
  It is necessary to secure maximum efforts, a major sense of 
responsibility, and emergency operational conditions in order 
for Georgia to have a single and strong Georgian Army. 
  Special attention has been attached to problems revealed 
during the inspection of the 11th brigade. It has been 
indicated that the leadership of the republic demonstrates deep 
concern over the establishment of the country's regular army. 
Special attention toward military units will be increased. 
  This information was supplied by the Defense Ministry press 
service. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

