<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze Rules on Holding Economic Forum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shevardnadze Rules on Holding Economic Forum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606151694 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1300 
GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2606151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Decree by the head of state of Georgia: 
  On measures for preparing a Russian-Georgian conference on 
the issues of economic cooperation and investment, and with the 
aim of accomplishing economic agreements signed between Russia 
and Georgia, a Russian-Georgian conference will be held on 21-24 
July of the current year in Tbilisi. The following should be 
done to this end: 
  1. The management of ministries and departments of the 
Republic of Georgia, with the help of enterprises subordinate to 
them, are to guarantee, by 30 June, the preparation of data of 
those draft investments which are of mutual interest for 
Georgian-Russian cooperation. They are also to present 
suggestions as to which representatives of Russian enterprises 
will be invited to the conference. 
  2. Carrying out of the decree is to be monitored by Georgian 
Deputy Prime Minister Zurab Kervalishvili. 

</TEXT>

