<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze Appeals to EU Leaders for Economic Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shevardnadze Appeals to EU Leaders for Economic Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406182494 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1500 
GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406182494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The European Union [EU] summit is opening on the 
Greek island of Corfu on 24th June. Georgian head of state 
Eduard Shevardnadze has sent letters to the heads of 12 EU 
states and to European Commission chairman Jacques Delors. 
  The Georgian head of state reviewed the difficult economic 
situation in Georgia and dramatic aftermath of the Abkhazian 
conflict that has had an adverse effect on current affairs. 
Apart from that, the letters point out what is thought to be 
impeding the establishment of democracy and market economy in 
the former Soviet republics. And finally, the letters call for 
the heads of state to support a request that the EU grant aid to 
Georgia in the face of a difficult winter expected in the 
country due to insufficient stocks of fuel and bread. 
  Mr. Shevardnadze has indicated that a strategy to provide 
new 
independent states with economic assistance should be devised. 
This is essential for strengthening democracy and creating 
market economy in these countries, this being of major 
importance for stability worldwide. 

</TEXT>

