<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze Issues Edict To Promote Foreign Investment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shevardnadze Issues Edict To Promote Foreign Investment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2406182694 Tbilisi SAKARTVELOS RESPUBLIKA in Georgian 17 
Jun 94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> AU2406182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi SAKARTVELOS RESPUBLIKA </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Edict from Head of State Eduard Shevardnadze "on the State </F>
Coordination Commission for Promoting the Attraction and 
Realization of Foreign Investment and Credits"] 
  [Text] The Georgian head of state has issued a edict to 
implement in an effective way priority programs and projects 
aimed at reviving the Republic of Georgia's economy by means of 
foreign investment and credits. 
  The State Coordination Commission for Promoting the 
Attraction and Realization of Foreign Investment and Credits 
will continue its work with a new staff; its chairman will be 
Head of State Eduard Shevardnadze and its deputy chairman will 
be Otar Patsatsia, Republic of Georgia prime minister. 
  The commission's senior secretary is Tengiz Geleishvili, the 
Georgian head of state's adviser on questions concerning foreign 
economic relations. 
  The following export groups have been created within the 
State Coordination Commission for Promoting the Attraction and 
Realization of Foreign Investment and Credits: fuel and power, 
industry, agroindustrial, metallurgy, telecommunication systems, 
construction, health protection, science and technology, 
environmental protection complexes, and in the private sector 
sphere. 
  It is pointed out in the edict that the Republic of Georgia 
Ministry of Economy along with the Committee for Foreign 
Economic Relations will examine measures stipulated in the 
anticrisis program and, proceeding from the interests of the 
republic's economy, will submit top-priority programs to the 
commission within two weeks; it is expedient to implement them 
with foreign investment and credits. 
  To prepare a general plan of work, the heads of the export 
groups will elaborate within two weeks a calendar plan for 
examining investment projects in accordance with top-priority 
programs and will prepare detailed proposals concerning 
individual projects. 
  [Signed] E. Shevardnadze. 

</TEXT>

