<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk, Zlenko Receive Thanks From Yeltsin, Kozyrev </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk, Zlenko Receive Thanks From Yeltsin, Kozyrev </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406182694 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1600 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk and Foreign 
Minister Anatoliy Zlenko have received telegrams from Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin and Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev. In 
the telegrams Boris Yeltsin and Andrey Kozyrev express their 
gratitude for the congratulations and good wishes in connection 
with Russia's national holiday--the Adoption of the Declaration 
of the Russian Federation's Sovereignty Day. 
  In his telegram, President Yeltsin confirmed Russia's desire 
to develop friendly all-round relations with fraternal Ukraine 
unwaveringly in the name of the well-being of the peoples of our 
two countries. 
  Minister Kozyrev expressed his confidence that the 
development of mutually advantageous interstate relations 
between Russia and Ukraine will further promote consolidation of 
friendship and mutual understanding between the nations of the 
two countries, contribute to achieving security and stability in 
Europe and the world over. 

</TEXT>

