<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Welcomes EU Funds To Shut Down Chernobyl </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk Welcomes EU Funds To Shut Down Chernobyl </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606225094 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1900 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2606225094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The problem of the Chernobyl AES [Nuclear Electric 
Power Station] is of exceptional importance not only for Ukraine 
but also for the entire world. This is why we welcome the 
decision by a session of the European Union council [word 
indistinct] to allocate 500 million ECU's to implement the plan 
to completely shut down the Chernobyl AES. It is important to 
check this amount continuously. 
  This was how Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk commented 
on 
the decision by a session of the European Union council. He 
said that, it was first necessary to resolve the issue of [words 
indistinct]. At the moment, we do not yet know how much will be 
needed in order to resolve the fate of the Chernobyl AES, 
Kravchuk stressed. 

