<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kuchma To Take Economic Measures First If Elected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kuchma To Take Economic Measures First If Elected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606140094 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1235 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2606140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- To the question from a UNIAN correspondent: 
"What will you do if you find out that you have been elected 
president of Ukraine or that you have gone through to the second 
round of the election," Leonid Kuchma, a candidate for president 
of Ukraine, noted: "If I am not elected, I would cross myself 
with happiness." In the event of his election he would take his 
first steps in the economy because "the point from which one 
should begin is to bring order to one's home." 
  With regard to possible cooperation with Vitaliy Masol, 
prime 
minister of Ukraine, if he is elected president, Leonid Kuchma 
replied that this is a question to which he does not yet know 
the answer at the moment. 

</TEXT>

