<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kuchma Urges Free Economic Zone Status for Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kuchma Urges Free Economic Zone Status for Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506083994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0709 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2506083994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM correspondent Lev Ryabchikov for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Simferopol 25 June TASS -- The Crimea, remaining an 
integral part of Ukraine, should become a free economic zone, a 
sort of a launching site for the economic processes, which will 
later be adopted by the whole of Ukraine, Leonid Kuchma said 
here on Friday [24 June]. The Crimea became the last region he 
visited in the course of his tour of Ukraine as a presidential 
candidate. 
  The Ukrainian ex-prime minister, who, according to the 
results of some public opinion polls, is the second most popular 
politician after President Kravchuk, had meetings with electors 
at industrial enterprises and farms and held talks with senior 
officials from the Crimean Government. 
  Speaking at a press conference, Kuchma said that he liked 
the 
reforms which are being worked out in the Crimea. He expressed 
confidence that the Crimea could not be brought back to its 
previous state, that of one of Ukraine's regions. When tackling 
controversial problems, it is necessary to take into 
consideration the real situation, the characteristic features of 
each particular region, he said. In his opinion, talks between 
Ukraine and the Crimea should be on the same level as between 
Russia and Tatarstan. 

</TEXT>

