<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk To Use Other Candidates' Ideas If Elected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk To Use Other Candidates' Ideas If Elected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606134894 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1235 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2606134894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- In reply to the question from a UNIAN 
correspondent, "What will you do if you find out that you have 
been elected president of Ukraine or that you have gone through 
to the second round," Leonid Kravchuk said: "If I am at home at 
the time, I will have a glass of cognac. If I am at work, I 
think I may do the same, and then I will get on with ordinary 
matters." According to Leonid Kravchuk, the question "What will 
you do if you find out you have been elected president" is a 
problem for the other candidates for president. For all his 
brilliant imaginings about the presidency, another candidate 
does not know what steps to take, while Kravchuk has been taking 
these first steps for two and a half years; therefore, he does 
not have this problem, he says. 
  Leonid Kravchuk sees his priority actions in the event of 
his 
election to president of Ukraine as implementing his program, 
while making use of all of the best points from the programs of 
the other candidates for this post, and also the formation of a 
government. 
  Leonid Kravchuk considers his cooperation with Vitaliy 
Masol, 
Ukraine's prime minister, to be "normal," observing that Masol 
is not a "closed book" to him, because they once worked 
together. "Of all the contenders for the post of president of 
Ukraine, only I know him, and therefore I do not have a 'Masol 
problem.' If someone else is elected, however, then he will 
have this problem," Leonid Kravchuk said. 

</TEXT>

