<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk: Ukraine Will `March the Road' of Reforms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk: Ukraine Will `March the Road' of Reforms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606110894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1055 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2606110894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev 26 June TASS -- "Ukraine will march the road of 
radical political and economic reforms. This is for sure. We 
have no other way if we want to build an economically strong and 
independent state and if we want to improve the life of people," 
incumbent President Leonid Kravchuk said in reply to journalists 
after casting balloting papers at one of Kiev's polling stations 
on Sunday. 
  "If I'm elected president, I shall continue reforms, shall 
work to resolve all difficult issues concerning the state and 
the government," he continued. 
  He stressed that special attention "will be given to 
privatisation, a change in currency regulation, the tax system, 
price formation, labour remuneration and pensions. 
  "It will be necessary to tackle urgently also foreign 
economic problems: Customs houses, customs duties, relations 
with other states and stimulation of exports to earn hard 
currency." 

</TEXT>

