<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Electoral Law Violations Reported in Odessa Rayons </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Electoral Law Violations Reported in Odessa Rayons </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706084494 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 0700 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706084494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Odessa, 26 Jun -- The "Ukrayina" Oblast Electoral 
Committee has received telephone calls about violations of the 
Electoral Law. For example, at most polling stations in 
Suvorovskiy, Kievskiy and Ilyichevskiy rayons of Odessa, the 
election posters of Vladlen Ilyin, representative of the 
president in Odessa oblast and candidate for the post of oblast 
council chairman, were removed, while posters of his rival, 
Ruslan Bodelan, were prominently displayed at all polling 
stations. 
  There was open electioneering for Lev Vershynin, candidate 
for deputy to Odessa town council, and Leonid Kuchma, candidate 
for president of Ukraine, at polling station No. 18 of central 
electoral district 366 of the town of Odessa. When an observer 
remarked on this, the response was a threat to call the militia. 

</TEXT>

