<H3> <TI>   Kuchma Wants To Lease Black Sea Fleet in Energy Exchange </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kuchma Wants To Lease Black Sea Fleet in Energy Exchange </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406230394 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2100 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406230394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Simferopol, 24 June -- Presidential Candidate Leonid 
Kuchma visited the Republic of Crimea. In Kerch, he met the 
director corps and employees of the Kerch Metallurgical Combine 
lease association and the "Zatoka" ship-building works (an 
enterprise in the military-industrial complex). 
  His meeting with the Crimean Republic's agrarians took place 
in Simferopolskiy rayon. Professor Serhiy Nikolskyy, Crimea's 
minister of agriculture and food, took part in the meeting. 
  At a meeting with voters Leonid Kuchma said that if he 
becomes president of Ukraine he will resolve the problem of the 
Black Sea Fleet by leasing it out on condition of receiving free 
energy carriers from Russia, and blamed the previous government 
and parliament for the ratification of the START-1 Treaty, in 
accordance with which Ukraine lost nuclear fuel, which according 
to Leonid Kuchma would have been sufficient for six or seven 
years. 

</TEXT>

