<H3> <TI>   Nationalists Set Up Antifascist Committee </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nationalists Set Up Antifascist Committee </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406101794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0844 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406101794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Nekrasova] </F>
  [Text] Lvov 24 June TASS -- The Ukrainian National Assembly 
(UNA), which has a combat paramilitary organisation UNSO 
(People's Self-Defence), has become the initiator of the 
formation of an anti-fascist committee and appointed Oleg 
Vitovich, a nationalist from Lvov and people's deputy to the 
Ukrainian parliament, as committee chairman. 
  UNA leader Anatoliy Lupynis, in an interview with the UNIAN 
news agency, said the democrats and liberals were the 
locomotives of political fascistisation in Ukraine. 
  It is noteworthy that it is precisely the selfsame democrats 
and liberals who refer to the UNA-UNSO organisation as a modern 
neonazi one, because its militants participated in the recent 
military conflicts in the Dniester region, Georgia, 
interconfessional strife inside the state, and now leave for the 
Crimea for summer "holidays." 

</TEXT>

