<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Masol Urges Consensus; To Propose Government Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Masol Urges Consensus; To Propose Government Members </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2606093794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0905 
GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2606093794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Melnik, Ukrinform </F>
correspondent Raisa Stetsura] 
  [Text] Kiev, 26 Jun -- "I am giving my vote to the 
democratic, rule-of-law, independent, and self-governing 
Ukraine, to an economically powerful state in which my people 
will live much better," said Ukraine's Prime Minister Vitaliy 
Masol today commenting on his participation in the presidential 
and local election. 
  In an interview to journalists at a polling station, he 
spoke 
in favor of cooperation between all branches of power in 
Ukraine. "If there is no such consensus, we will be unable to 
avoid certain collisions," he said. 
  Vitaliy Masol said that apart from the election results, he 
would soon propose at the parliament the list of government 
members. The prime minister declined to comment on a possible 
cabinet reshuffle. 

</TEXT>

