<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Yeltsin Attending EU Meeting in Corfu </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Yeltsin Attending EU Meeting in Corfu </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Agree on Troop Leaving Ceremony </H4>

<F P=102> LD2406192294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1812 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2406192294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Kulbitskiy] </F>
  [Text] Bonn June 24 TASS -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin 
and German Federal Chancellor Helmut Kohl have managed to agree 
on details of the seeing-off ceremony for Russian troops 
withdrawn from Germany during their meeting in Kerkira (Corfu), 
official representative of the German Government Dieter Vogel 
told German news agencies today. 
  Under the agreement, Boris Yeltsin and Helmut Kohl will take 
the parade of the Russian troops on August 31, 1994. Vogel made 
no further comments on the issue. He said that the Kerkira 
summit is not the best place to do it. All the details will be 
made public early next week upon Vogel's return to Bonn. 

</TEXT>

