<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Yeltsin Attending EU Meeting in Corfu </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Yeltsin Attending EU Meeting in Corfu </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Yeltsin Calls Agreement `Historic' </H4>

<F P=102> LD2506171494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1634 
GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2506171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Athens, 25 Jun -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin 
described as "historic" the agreement on partnership and 
cooperation between the Russian Federation and the European 
Union signed on 24 June on the island of Corfu. He made this 
statement while answering questions from journalists at Athens 
airport before his departure to Russia. 
  A really historic document has been signed, he said. It was 
under preparation for a very long time, almost two years. 
Europe is now the only continent that has lifted all 
discriminatory measures against Russia. Indeed Russia, of 
course, gets certain dividends from this. The states of Europe 
get a very rich Russian market, and they too, will not lose out 
by having signed this document. 
  The president thanked the Greek leadership and Greek Prime 
Minister Andreas Papandreou for their involvement in the 
preparation of the agreement, and for creating most favorable 
conditions for the work of the Russian delegation. 

</TEXT>

