<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tengiz Pachkoria] </F>
  [Text] Zugdidi (western Georgia) June 24 TASS -- Two 
battalions of Russian peackeepers with about a hundred motor 
vehicles and armoured personnel carriers arrived in the 
afternoon on Friday in the Zugdidi area. 
  Peacekeepers who came from the Russian base in the Georgian 
city of Batumi, were met by friendly local population and their 
drivers saluted back blowing their horns. 

