<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Black Sea Fleet: Moscow, Kiev Do Not Support Joint Command </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Black Sea Fleet: Moscow, Kiev Do Not Support Joint Command </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406181094 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 
1500 GMT 24 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2406181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The proposal by Aleksandr Moroz, the chairman of the 
Ukrainian Supreme Council, that the Black Sea Fleet should have 
a joint command has won no support either in Kiev or in Moscow, 
Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk said today. According to 
him, if the combined fleet continues to exist, peace will never 
be achieved. 

</TEXT>

