<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chinese Fishermen Detained, Fined for Illegal Fishing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chinese Fishermen Detained, Fined for Illegal Fishing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706151994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1322 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A Chinese fishing boat was detained for illegally 
fishing in Russian territorial waters on Sunday. 
  The arrest follows an operation codenamed Zaslon against 
poaching and illegal border crossing, launched by the Far 
Eastern Border District last Thursday. 
  The amount of fines imposed on Russian and foreign vessels 
since the launching of the operation runs at Rbl 1 billion. 
More than Rbl 230 million worth of smuggled goods were seized 
and 38 people, most of them Chinese, were detained for illegal 
border crossing. 
  Out of 36 Russian vessels inspected, one was impounded on 
charges of trying to smuggle out a load of non-ferrous metal and 
large diameter pipes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

