<H3> <TI>   Kazimirov Says Russia, CSCE Have Same Goals in Karabakh </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kazimirov Says Russia, CSCE Have Same Goals in Karabakh </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706192994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1836 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia and the CSCE are applying similar efforts to 
settle the Nagorno-Karabakh conflict, Russian presidential 
representative Vladimir Kazimirov stated at a news conference in 
Yerevan Monday. At the same time, the Russian peace settlement 
plan envisioned more guarantees ensuring the mechanism for 
cease-fire than the one proposed by the CSCE, he said. 
  Kazimiriov dismissed speculation that the CSCE and Russia 
had 
differences over the settlement issue. Russia should coordinate 
its efforts with the CSCE, he said. Work is going on to convert 
the Russian plan into a true agreement, a legal document which 
could be signed at a top level, rather than a schedule of 
immediate measures, he said. 
  Kazimirov said the main priority of the Russian plan was to 
develop a mechanism to establish a cease-fire, which is 
essential for moving towards a Nagorno-Karabakh peace settlement. 
  Kazimirov also met Armenian President Levon Ter- Petrosian. 
He told Interfax after the meeting that he was satisfied with 
its results. "Much has been clarified," he said. 

</TEXT>

