<H3> <TI>   Credit Agreement Signed With Mexican Foreign Trade Bank </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Credit Agreement Signed With Mexican Foreign Trade Bank </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806085694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0813 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2806085694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksey Kravchenko] </F>
  [Text] Mexico City June 28 TASS -- The National Bank for 
Foreign Trade of Mexico and the Russian foreign trade 
amalgamation "Energomasheksport" here on Monday signed an 
agreement on opening a credit line for Russian enterprises and 
companies for acquiring goods in this Latin American country. 
  The document envisages the possibility of receiving credits 
for exports to Russia goods worth 2 million U.S. dollars. The 
sides can increase the financial support up to 10 million 
dollars, according to their mutual understanding. Now Russian 
firms, which wish to make use of credit lines for imports of 
Mexican agricultural, consumer and industrial goods, will have 
to approach the "Energomasheksport". 
  This agreement creates an important precedent in bilateral 
ties, Anatoliy Yevdakomov, adviser to the Russian trade 
representation, told ITAR-TASS. Earlier this practice was used 
exclusively by state establishments of the former Soviet Union. 
Now the Mexican side is for the first time using this mutually 
beneficial financial mechanism for the development of economic 
exchange with Russia, he said. 

</TEXT>

