<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The unfinished aircraft carrier Varyag, moored in 
the Nikolayev harbor in the Black Sea, will in all probability 
have to be scrapped. The scrapping will cost $174.6 million and 
take 4.5 years to complete. Even though some quarters have 
expressed interest in buying the vessel, any plans to sell it 
are hampered by the existing agreement between Russia and 
Ukraine, under which vessels of this type cannot be sold to a 
third country. 

