<F P=106> [Report by Aleksandr Bugay from the "Fax News" roundup in </F>
the "Russkoye Oruzhiye" section: "`Mailbox Numbers' Need Help"] 
  [Text] Kazan -- Defense enterprises in Tataria [Tatarstan] 
have found themselves in the gravest of socioeconomic positions. 
According to M. Shakhmeyev, chairman of the Radio-Electronic 
Workers Trade Union Republic Committee, one-half of the 130,000 
workers at former "mailbox number" enterprises are currently 
working on a reduced schedule. 
  At gatherings of workers' collectives, which have taken 
place 
at virtually all defense enterprises, it has been proposed that 
the government and president of Tataria resolve the issue of 
financing conversion programs in full by 1 July, reserve in 
enterprise accounts for emergencies and the payment of wages no 
less than 30 percent of the amount of the payment, maintain 
contributions to the social insurance fund at a level of 5.4 
percent, and settle a number of other questions. 

