<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Accident Reported in Radioactive Waste Depository </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Accident Reported in Radioactive Waste Depository </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806024994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0150 
GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806024994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Borovkov] </F>
  [Text] Petropavlovsk-Kamchatskiy, 28 Jun (TASS) -- An 
accident has occurred at the radioactive wastes depository 
situated on the shore of Seldevaya bay not far from 
Petropavlovsk-Kamchatskiy. Two slabs from the covering were 
damaged from being washed with water from melted snow and have 
caved in. This has been reported in today's issue of IZVESTIYA, 
quoting the heads of the oblast headquarters of the civil 
defense. According to these data, the radiation directly above 
the crack that has formed is eight milliroentgens, that is 1,000 
times higher than the natural background for Kamchatka. 
  However, the heads of the civil defense headquarters think 
that this radiation does not present a danger to the residents 
of the oblast centre and the neighboring settlements: it is 
local and "fades away" at a distance of a few meters. At the 
present time repair work is being carried out at the burial 
ground. 
  What is more, no one has managed to get complete and 
objective information about the the situation at the storage 
yet: admission to this secret facility which belongs to the 
nuclear submarine flotilla, is closed to all civil inspectors. 
Even the information that the civil defense headquarters has at 
its disposal has been obtained from navy sailors. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

