<H3> <TI>   CSCE Mission To Extend Mandate by 6 Months </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CSCE Mission To Extend Mandate by 6 Months </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2806092994 Tallinn ETA in English 0653 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2806092994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the 28 Jun EESTI SENUMID, p.3; "News Bulletin" No. </F>
122/94] 
  [Text] The CSCE permanent committee in Vienna will extend 
the mandate of the CSCE mission in Estonia by six months from 
July 1. Representatives of several countries pointed out that 
the mission should also pay more attention to the monitoring of 
the Russian troops withdrawal, the Foreign Ministry press 
service announced. 
  The Estonian delegation to the CSCE permanent committee also 
started a discussion of the Estonian-Russian border issue in 
connection with the Russian presidential decree on the 
unilateral marking of the border line. The delegation stressed 
that border issues must be settled via bilateral negotiations, 
according to the CSCE principles and other international 
standards. No resolution was passed due to lack of consensus on 
the issue. 

</TEXT>

