<H3> <TI>   Landsbergis on Military Transit Agreement With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Landsbergis on Military Transit Agreement With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2806095594 Vilnius ELTA in English 1911 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2806095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius ELTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From "News Bulletin" No. 530 ] </F>
  [Text] Vilnius, June 27, ELTA -- Opposition leader 
Vytautas Landsbergis made a statement on the 
Lithuanian-Russian agreement on military transit. 
  Landsbergis claimed in his statement that "during the 
recent days some governmental statements on Russian military 
transit via Lithuania have caused great concerns". 
  Head of negotiation group Bulovas said that the agreement 
which had been proposed by Russia could be signed after two 
weeks when Lithuania established transit rules for 
dangerous and military cargoes. 
  According to the statement, "President thinks that transits 
for all partners should be legalized as soon as possible. As I 
can see no logics in such statements, they possibly 
include something that should be known by Lithuanian people 
before our country finds itself entangled into the Russian 
military system". 
  "Lithuanian labour democratic party has no mandate to 
condemn the whole nation", Landsbergis said. 

</TEXT>

