<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Jun 27, BNS -- Lithuanian President 
Algirdas Brazauskas' popularity rating increased by 2 percent in 
June after a sharp drop in May, according to the results of a 
public opinion poll conducted June 8-15 by the 
British-Lithuanian Baltic Surveys. 
  But the survey indicates that Lithuanians continue to lose 
confidence in nearly all other political leaders, with the 
exception of the chairman of the opposition Conservative Party's 
board, Gediminas Vagnorius, whose rating jumped by 5 percent. 
Vagnorius is now ahead of Prime Minister Adolfas Slezevicius 
and the Conservative Party leader, Vytautas Landsbergis. 
  Centrists Egidijus Bickauskas and Romualdas Ozolas retained 
second and third positions. Like earlier, the popularity lists 
ends with Foreign Minister Povilas Gylys, even though his 
popularity went up by 1 percent. 
  According to the results, the most popular politicians in 
June were: 


