<F P=106> [By unidentified ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 27 Jun -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin 
met members of the Russian Agrarian Party group in the Kremlin 
today. The deputies briefed the president on their group's 
organizational structure and its numerical strength, as well as 
on their political positions, which they describe as centrist. 
The conversation was devoted to problems of the agro-industrial 
complex. 
  Having noted his full awareness of the difficulties Russian 
agriculture was experiencing, the president stressed the need to 
develop the agro-industrial complex taking account of the 
overall strategy of the country's economic reforms. 
  It was agreed to continue contacts between presidential 
structures and the State Duma's groups, including the Agrarian 
Party group, to prepare agreed decisions, the Russian 
president's press service told ITAR-TASS. 

