  [Text] Russia's agriculture should be reformed on the basis 
of freedom to choose form of property, Russian Presidential 
Advisor Georgy Satarov told Interfax Monday commenting on the 
results of Boris Yeltsin's meeting with the leaders of the 
Agrarian Party of Russia and its parliamentary faction this 
afternoon. He cited Yeltsin as saying that no imposition could 
be exercised in this issue. 
