and its parliamentary faction, Mikhail Lapshin, and a group of 
agrarian deputies. 
  Satarov said the participants of the meeting came to the 
conclusion that such meetings should be held regularly as they 
promoted the process of "joint shaping up a balanced policy for 
agrarian reforms in Russia." 

