<H3> <TI>   Constitutional Court Protection Department Created </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Constitutional Court Protection Department Created </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706193894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1837 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706193894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin signed a decree on 
setting up a department for the protection of the Constitutional 
Court under the Federal Counterintelligence Service Monday. 
  The presidential press office said the decree had been 
issued 
in accordance with the Russian law on the protection of top 
state bodies and officials. The department will coordinate its 
activities with other federal protection, counterintelligence 
and interior and state security bodies as well as the 
administration and leaders of enterprises regardless of their 
form of property. 
  The decree came into force once signed. 

</TEXT>

