<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Approximately 1 Percent Reported Jobless </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Approximately 1 Percent Reported Jobless </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706155994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1533 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706155994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yekaterina Zhilyakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 27 TASS -- Practically one in a hundred 
Russians is unemployed or is registered by the state employment 
agency as "not being occupied by working activity," i.e, 
jobless. Most of the Russian unemployed are women and unskilled 
workers, since those are the ones most often laid off. 
  Statistics show that there are almost one and a half million 
jobless in Russia now. One million 219 thousand of them had 
been officially recognized as unemployed. Two out of every 
three people on the dole are former unskilled labourers. 
  Women are the unluckiest of all in the job market. 
Two-thirds of the jobless are women. Moreover, the youngest 
seem to suffer disproportionately: every third is in the 16-29 
age group. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

