<H3> <TI>   Mir Cosmonauts Continue Mission </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mir Cosmonauts Continue Mission </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806103694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1029 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2806103694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Mission Control Centre June 28 TASS -- Russian 
cosmonauts Viktor Afanasyev, Yuriy Usachev and Valeriy Polyakov 
are carrying on their mission on board the orbital complex Mir. 
  They carried out several sessions of photography of various 
regions of the planet under the environmental study programme. 
Photography is to be continued on Tuesday. 
  The mission commander with the help of the research 
physician 
will undergo a comprehensive examination of the cardiovascular 
system by an ultrasonic method with the use of the 
pneumatic-vacuum space suit Chibis. Technical maintenance of 
equipment and instruments of the station is also planned. 
  The handling of the progress M-23 automatic cargo spacecraft 
is being finalised. On Monday the joint propulsion plant of the 
station was refuelled and the second fuel component -- oxidiser 
-- is to be pumped on Tuesday. 
  According to reports from orbit, the flight is proceeding 
normally and the cosmonauts are feeling well. 

</TEXT>

