<F P=102>   LD2806063194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0623 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2806063194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tigran Liloyan] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan June 28 TASS -- Russian presidential envoy 
to Nagorno-Karabakh Vladimir Kazimirov is leaving Baku for 
Ankara on Tuesday to hold talks with Turkish authorities on the 
disputed enclave. 
  Speaking in Yerevan on Monday Kazimirov said that the talks 
"are routine consultations which have no sensations or special 
turns". 
  The envoy rejected the idea that contacts with Turkey and 
Iran "create a new format for talks in the regional aspect". He 
said his recent trip to Tehran and the upcoming visit to Ankara 
are made in return to the talks of diplomats of the two 
countries recently held in Moscow. 
  Kazimirov recalled that combat activities had been held 
right 
on the Iranian border with Azerbaijan going along the Arax 
river. He said this was a "very aggravating circumstance" which 
can make the conflict spread to other countries. "that is why 
the position of iran is an important factor and we take it into 
consideration", the envoy stressed. 

</TEXT>

