<H3> <TI>   Karabakh Defense HQ Cited on Azerbaijani Shelling </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karabakh Defense HQ Cited on Azerbaijani Shelling </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2806103594 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN in 
English 0719 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2806103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert ("AZG", "LRAGIR" dailies), 06/28/94--The 
situation at the Karabakh fronts remains unchanged. 
  According to the RMK [Republic of Mountainous Karabakh] 
defense army headquarters, the Azeri units continue shelling the 
Karabakh defense positions in the Mardakertskiy and Agdamskiy 
districts. The Karabakh units have been refraining from 
returning the fire. 
  RMK military reconnaissance reports significant 
concentration 
and movements of the Azeri manpower and equipment in the 
direction of the settlement of Agburun in the Martuninskiy 
district. 
  "The RMK National Security Department has reliable 
information about a new offensive, being prepared against 
Karabakh by Azerbaijan," said Chairman of the department Kamo 
Abrahamyan. He reported that new army summons have started in 
Azerbaijan a few days ago. Men of different age groups are 
called up to the army. At the same time, new batches of 
weaponry, ammunition and food are being received from Turkey and 
Ukraine. This all, as well as regrouping of enemy forces at the 
fronts is evidence that the Azeri Government is not serious 
about CSCE and Russian peace projects. 

</TEXT>

