<H3> <TI>   Agreement Signed With Russia on Joint Oil Prospecting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agreement Signed With Russia on Joint Oil Prospecting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2706211994 Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1900 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2706211994 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Armenia's Radio First Program Network 
in Armenian 1900 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Armenian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Armenian State Directorate for Underground Resources 
and the Russian Committee for Geology and Exploitation of 
Underground Resources signed an agreement in Moscow on 
cooperation in the geological study and exploitation of 
underground resources. 
  The principal aim of the agreement is to draw up and 
implement a mutually-advantageous policy for the geological 
study of the underground resources. 
  In accordance with one of the points in that agreement, a 
protocol was also signed in Moscow on the Armenian Republic's 
participation in the exploitation of oil and gas fields in 
Russia. The Armenian side is mostly interested in participating 
in the exploitation of one of the oil and gas fields in western 
Russia. It will make certain investments and participate in the 
work by establishing an Armenian-Russian joint venture with any 
Russian organization certified to exploit the underground 
resources. 
  In return, the Armenian side is ready to examine the issue 
of 
the participation of the Russian enterprises in the geological 
study and exploitation of the oil and gas fields in Armenia. 

</TEXT>

