<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Killing of 15 Kurd-Yezidis in Armenia Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Killing of 15 Kurd-Yezidis in Armenia Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2706200094 Baku TURAN in English 1604 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2706200094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku (June 27) TURAN -- Over 15 Kurds-Yezidis were 
violently killed during the clashes on the ethnic base between 
the Kurd-yezids population of Garalar village of Araratskiy 
region in Armenia and group of armed Armenians, who came from 
Yerevan. TURAN was told by informed source that the clash took 
place in the middle of June, when some representatives of Kurd 
Working Party [PKK], functioning in the republic, were arrested 
by Armenian authorities. 
  This event sharpened the complicated social and political 
situation in Armenia. The Kurds again remember the violent 
murder of Said Ibon, famous pediatrist, Kurd by nationality, 
killed by Armenians in 1991 in his office. 
  According to information, Levon Ter-Petrosyan, Armenian 
president, ordered to deploy special forces and military 
hardware imto Garalar village and other regions where Kurd 
population live. The troops were ordered to open fire, if any 
attempts of counterraction on the part of local Kurd population 
take place. 

</TEXT>

