<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dniester Officers Allegedly To Train Crimean Soldiers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dniester Officers Allegedly To Train Crimean Soldiers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2706145194 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2228 GMT 23 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2706145194 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tiraspol, ROMPRES, 23/06/1994 -- Informed sources 
from the 14th Army told BASA that a group of 30 officers of the 
Dniester Security Ministry had left for Crimea. The group is 
assigned to take part in preparing the soldiers of the Crimean 
Interior Ministry to carry out certain military operations. 
Sources from the Dniester security told BASA that such 
information is totally unfounded. The same sources stated that 
the spreading of such rumors is part of the campaign to 
discredit Tiraspol officials. Earlier, it was said that a group 
of eight officers of the "Delfin" detachment and "Dniestr" 
battalion of the Dniester Interior Ministry were sent in 1993 to 
Abkhazia to organize diversions in the rear of the Georgian 
Army. Sources from the 14th Army said that the Abkhazian defense 
minister sent a letter to the Tiraspol Interior Ministry 
recommending promotion of the officers of the "Dniester" 
battalion who took part in military operations in Abkhazia. 

</TEXT>

