<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Says Army `Not Interested' in Resolving Conflict </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Says Army `Not Interested' in Resolving Conflict </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2706144594 Moscow NOVAYA YEZHEDNEVNAYA GAZETA in Russian 
25 Jun 94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM2706144594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NOVAYA YEZHEDNEVNAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [INTERFAX report: "The 14th Army Likes It in the Dniester </F>
Region"] 
  [Text] At a news conference held in Moscow Igor Smirnov, 
president of the self-proclaimed Dniester Moldavian [Moldovan] 
Republic [DMR], declared that "individuals in the 14th Army are 
not interested in resolving the conflict" between Moldavia 
[Moldova] and the DMR. He based his opinion on the argument 
that the wages of a 14th Army officer stand at 300,000 Russian 
rubles, i.e. 1.5 million former Soviet rubles, which are the 
basic monetary unit in the DMR. Therefore, officers would not 
like to leave the Dniester region. 

</TEXT>

