<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gas Imports Reduced Due to Nonpayments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gas Imports Reduced Due to Nonpayments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806095594 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 0805 
GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2806095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Due to the nonpayment of a large debt for natural 
gas consumption and delivery, the supply of natural gas to the 
republic was reduced by 60 percent as of 27 June 1994. 
  Instead of receiving 7.5m cubic meters of gas a day, the 
republic will now be receiving 3.0m cubic meters. The Sakgazi 
Department will distribute this limited supply among vital 
installations in the republic, including Tbilisi power station, 
which will be receiving 1.0m cubic meters of gas a day, instead 
of the required 3.0m cubic meters. 
  All supplies of natural gas to eastern and western Georgian 
regions and to the Kartli and Kvemo Kartli zones will be stopped 
as of today. 
  As soon as the situation improves the Sakgazi Department 
will 
take measures to resume the normal supply of gas. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

