<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Preliminary Talks on Accord With EU </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Preliminary Talks on Accord With EU </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706194294 Tbilisi First Program Television Network in 
Georgian 1600 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2706194294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi First Program Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The press secretariat of the Georgian Foreign 
Ministry reports that preliminary talks on the preparation of a 
partnership and cooperation agreement between Georgia and the 
European Union [EU] were held in Brussels on 23 and 24 June. 
This document will define economic relations between Georgia 
and the EU and will be vivid evidence of the EU's intention to 
include Georgia in the European economic and banking system. 
The agreement will grant Georgia most favored nation treatment 
in trade. 
  The Georgian delegation at the meeting was headed by Mikheil 
Ukleba, first deputy foreign minister. [passage omitted] 
  The first round of negotiations between the Republic of 
Georgia and the EU will be held in September. 

</TEXT>

