<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Communist Party Holds Congress; Member Dies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Communist Party Holds Congress; Member Dies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2506165194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1510 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2506165194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The first constituent congress of the renewed 
Communist Party of Georgia was held on Saturday in Tbilisi. 
  While opening the congress, retired general Panteleimon 
Georgadze, leader of the party, declared that the aims of the 
communists "remain unchanged -- creation of a free equal society 
and protection of the interests of the working people. We want 
to return achievements of socialism," he stressed. 
  While addressing the congress, Filipp Makharadze, veteran of 
Georgia' Communist Party and former director of Lenin's museum 
in Georgia, died just on the rostrum. However, this tragic 
incident has not interrupted the congress. 
  A representative of the Armenian communists who attended the 
congress declared that it "is a death worthy of a communist." 

</TEXT>

