<H3> <TI>   Communist Party Elects First Secretary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Communist Party Elects First Secretary </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706151294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1417 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706151294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By GIA-ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Tbilisi] June 27 TASS -- The first congress of the joint 
Communist Party of Georgia brought together 550 delegates in 
Tbilisi. 
  Retired major general Panteleimon Giorgadze presided over 
the 
congress. He was elected first secretary of the joint Communist 
Party of Georgia by the delegates. 
  "Our aim is to be represented in parliament, and to become 
the country's ruling party. To achieve it, unification is 
necessary. Delegates from the Workers' Communist Party of 
Georgia, the Georgian Union of Communists, the "Stalin" 
political organization and a public organization called the 
International Society to Honour the Memory of Stalin 
participated in the congress. There are no differences in their 
standpoints, which enabled us to form a joint Communist Party," 
Giorgadze told GIA on Monday. 

</TEXT>

