<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Current Election Results Show Kravchuk Leading Kuchma </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Current Election Results Show Kravchuk Leading Kuchma </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kravchuk Leads in 14 Oblasts, Kuchma in 7 </H4>

<F P=102> LD2706132394 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1115 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706132394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- On 27 June UNIAN learned preliminary data 
about the voting in various oblasts for candidates in the 
presidential election. This data was received from oblast 
electoral commissions for the presidential election and from 
oblast councils of people's deputies. UNIAN also received 
preliminary data from the Central Electoral Commission for the 
election of a president of Ukraine. In most cases the data does 
not include several rayons in each oblast. 
  Leonid Kravchuk received more votes than the other 
candidates 
for president in the following oblasts: Vinnitsa, Volyn, 
Zhitomir, Ivano-Frankovsk, Rovno, Kiev, Kirovograd, Lvov, Sumy, 
Ternopol, Khmelnitskiy, Cherkassy, Chernovtsy, and 
Transcarpathia Oblasts and the city of Kiev. 
  Leonid Kuchma received more votes than the other candidates 
in the following oblasts: Dnepropetrovsk, Donetsk, Zaporozhye, 
Lugansk, Nikolayev, Odessa, Chernigov oblasts, the Republic of 
Crimea, and the city of Sevastopol. 
  Information from Kharkov Oblast is being finalized. UNIAN 
has learned from reliable sources that the picture there is 
ambiguous; in some rayons Oleksandr Moroz is well in the lead, 
but in some rayons either Leonid Kravchuk or Leonid Kuchma is 
slightly in the lead. In the town of Izyum, Volodymyr Lanovyy 
received 23 percent. 
  Information on Kherson and Poltava Oblasts is being 
finalized. 

</TEXT>

