<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Wins 40 Percent, Kuchma 35 Percent of Rukh Votes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk Wins 40 Percent, Kuchma 35 Percent of Rukh Votes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2706143694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1405 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2706143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev 27 June TASS -- Ukrainian President "Leonid 
Kravchuk has won 40 per cent of votes in the presidential 
marathon, his major rival ex-Prime Minister Leonid Kuchma 35 per 
cent," Rukh nationalist movement leader Vyacheslav Chornovil 
said on Monday. 
  Chornovil said the information is based on reports from Rukh 
observers at polling stations. 
  Earlier today, reliable sources told ITAR-TASS on Monday [27 
June] that Kravchuk has taken the lead in 15 out of 24 Ukrainian 
regions in the nation's second presidential elections. 
  He was supported by the residents of the western, central 
and 
partially eastern and southern regions of Ukraine. 
  Kuchma has gained advantage over Kravchuk in the Crimea, the 
Donetsk, Lugansk, Dnepropetrovsk, Zaporozhye, Odessa, Kharkov 
and Chernigov regions. 
  Since the Central Electoral Commission has not announced the 
preliminary results of voting yet, journalists have to base 
their reports on information provided by regional electoral 
commissions and other sources. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

