<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kuchma To Contest Results, Alleges `Vote-Rigging' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kuchma To Contest Results, Alleges `Vote-Rigging' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2806081694 Paris AFP in English 0800 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2806081694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 28 June (AFP) -- Former Ukrainian premier 
Leonid Kuchma, challenging President Leonid Kravchuk in 
presidential elections here, will contest the validity of the 
first-round election result with an allegation of vote-rigging, 
a Kuchma aide said Tuesday [28 June]. 
  Pyotr Lemek accused several local electoral committees of 
falsifying votes to give Kravchuk an edge over Kuchma. A press 
conference of the central electoral committee scheduled for 
1100. (0800 GMT) Tuesday was delayed for several hours. 
  "Kuchma garnered 34 percent of the votes and Kravchuk 36 
percent, and the difference is not eight percentage points as 
(Kravchuk) aides maintain," he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

