<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report published under the rubric "Fact"] </F>
  [Text] Foreign specialists, who visited the "White 
Panther" [Bila Pantera] special-purpose battalion within the 
Kiev regiment of Ukraine's National Guard, were highly impressed 
by the level of training of the guards. One can imagine how 
surprised they might be if they had learned that the 
special-purpose guards' nourishment is worse than that of 
regular servicemen and that the average pay received by the 
commander of the battalion constitutes 400,000 coupons a month. 

</TEXT>

