<H3> <TI>   Future of Part-Built Aircraft Carrier Under Discussion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Future of Part-Built Aircraft Carrier Under Discussion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2806121994 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 28 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2806121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM-TASS: "Aircraft Carrier Varyag Will </F>
Not Be Scrapped"] 
  [Text] Reports appearing in the press that a decision has 
already been made to recycle the Varyag are untrue. 
  The most acceptable and advantageous option for deciding the 
aircraft carrier's future is to sell it in its present condition 
(68-percent finished), according to Ivan Vinnik, deputy general 
director of the Black Sea Shipbuilding Plant. Another possible 
option for using Varyag is to remove everything possible from it 
and to sell its hull for use as a cruiser or other vessel. We 
will not break up the Varyag out of morale considerations, Ivan 
Vinnik stressed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

