<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Joint Venture Recycling Obsolete Munitions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Joint Venture Recycling Obsolete Munitions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806105894 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2200 GMT 26 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2806105894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The recycling of Ukrainian ammunition which has 
exceeded its expiry date is now being conducted by the 
joint-stock company "Alliyant-Kiev," formed in 1993 by the 
Shostkinskiy scientific and research institute, the U.S. 
Alliyant-Tecsystems, and Repirbase Ltd of Great Britain. The 
Ukrainian partner has 51 per cent of the shares in the 
joint-stock company. In the first quarter, "Allyant- Kiev" 
already received 5,600 tonnes of ammunition for recycling. The 
127 tonnes of extracted gunpowder were sent to the UkrVybukhBud 
explosives manufacturer and the 250 tonnes of brass cartidges to 
a nonferrous reprocessing factory to be reprocessed into rolled 
metal. 
  According to unofficial sources at the Defense Ministry, 
there are 320,000 tonnes of ammunition stocks in line to be 
scrapped. 

</TEXT>

