<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Postpones Decision on Defense Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Postpones Decision on Defense Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2806091494 Tallinn BNS in English 1822 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2806091494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Tallinn, June 27, BNS -- Estonian President 
Lennart Meri today approved the nominations of Andres Lipstok as 
finance minister and Peeter Olesk as the minister of culture and 
education. But the president still left it open whether or not 
he will approve of the prime minister's nomination of Enn Tupp 
for the post of the defense minister. 
  Officials at the presidential chancellery were unable to say 
why the president had postponed his decision about Tupp's 
nomination. According to the Estonian laws, the president must 
announce his decision Tuesday at the latest. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

